Document: AudioEffectBandPassFilter
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectbandpassfilter.rst
Summary: A class that applies a band-pass filter to audio signals, allowing control over frequency range and resonance.

Inherits: AudioEffect < AudioFilter < AudioProcessor

This class provides a band-pass filter effect for audio processing. It allows you to specify the center frequency, bandwidth, and resonance of the filter. The effect can be used to shape the frequency content of audio signals in various ways, such as emphasizing a specific frequency range or attenuating frequencies outside a desired range.

Key parameters include:
- center_frequency (float): The center frequency of the band-pass filter in Hertz. Default: 1000.0
- bandwidth (float): The bandwidth of the filter in Hertz. Default: 200.0
- resonance (float): The resonance of the filter, which controls the sharpness of the frequency response. Default: 1.0

The filter operates in real-time and can be applied to audio streams using the AudioServer. It is part of Godot's audio processing pipeline and can be combined with other audio effects to create complex audio filters.

Note: The actual frequency response of the filter may vary depending on the audio hardware and the settings of the AudioServer.
